### Performing Reactive Query with useQuery Hook in React Native

Source: https://github.com/powersync-ja/powersync-js/blob/main/packages/react/README.md

Illustrates fetching data reactively using the `useQuery` hook. The hook takes a SQL query string, parameters, and options like `runQueryOnce`. It returns an object with `data`, which automatically updates when the underlying data changes. This specific example uses React Native components (`<View>`, `<Text>`). Requires the `@powersync/react` package.

```JSX
// TodoListDisplay.jsx
import { useQuery } from "@powersync/react";

export const TodoListDisplay = () => {
    const { data: todoLists } = useQuery('SELECT * FROM lists WHERE id = ?', ['id-1'], {runQueryOnce: false});

    return <View>
      {todoLists.map((l) => (
        <Text key={l.id}>{JSON.stringify(l)}</Text>
      ))}
    </View>
}
```

