### Configuring PowerSync Context Provider in React

Source: https://github.com/powersync-ja/powersync-js/blob/main/packages/react/README.md

Demonstrates initializing a PowerSync database client (web or React Native) and wrapping the application's components within `PowerSyncContext.Provider` to make the PowerSync instance accessible via hooks. Requires the `@powersync/web` or `@powersync/react-native` SDK and `@powersync/react`. The `powerSync` instance is created using `React.useMemo` for performance.

```JSX
// App.jsx
import { PowerSyncDatabase } from '@powersync/web';
// or for React Native
// import { PowerSyncDatabase } from '@powersync/react-native';
import { PowerSyncContext } from "@powersync/react";
export const App = () => {
    const powerSync = React.useMemo(() => {
        // Setup PowerSync client
    }, [])

    return <PowerSyncContext.Provider value={powerSync}>
        {/** Insert your components here */ }
    </PowerSyncContext.Provider>
}
```

