### Handling useQuery Loading and Fetching States in React

Source: https://github.com/powersync-ja/powersync-js/blob/main/packages/react/README.md

Shows how to destructure the `isLoading` and `isFetching` boolean flags from the `useQuery` hook's return object. These flags are used to conditionally render a loading message and control the opacity of the list display, providing visual feedback during data loading and re-fetching. Requires the `@powersync/react` package.

```JSX
// TodoListDisplay.jsx
import { useQuery } from "@powersync/react";

export const TodoListsDisplayDemo = () => {
  const { data: todoLists, isLoading, isFetching } = useQuery('SELECT * FROM lists');
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Todo Lists {isFetching ? '⟳' : ''}</h1>
      <div
        style={{
          opacity: isLoading ? 1 : 0,
          transition: 'opacity 0.5s ease-in-out'
        }}>
        Loading todo lists...
      </div>
      <ul
        style={{
          opacity: isLoading ? 0 : 1,
          transition: 'opacity 1s ease-in-out'
        }}>
        {todoLists.map(() => (
          <li key={l.id}>{JSON.stringify(l)}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  );
};
```

