### Configuring Metro to Block Inline Requires (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/powersync-ja/powersync-js/blob/main/packages/react-native/README.md

JavaScript code snippet for `metro.config.js` in bare React Native apps. This configuration prevents Metro from using inline requires for the `@powersync/react-native` package, addressing potential errors like "Super expression must either be null or a function".

```js
const config = {
  transformer: {
    getTransformOptions: async () => ({
      transform: {
        inlineRequires: {
          blockList: {
            [require.resolve('@powersync/react-native')]: true
          }
        }
      }
    })
  }
};
```

