### Accessing PowerSync Client with usePowerSync Hook

Source: https://github.com/powersync-ja/powersync-js/blob/main/packages/react/README.md

Shows how to retrieve the PowerSync database instance using the `usePowerSync` hook within a functional component. It then uses `powersync.getAll` to fetch all records from the 'lists' table asynchronously and updates the component state using `React.useState` and `React.useEffect`. Requires the `@powersync/react` package.

```JSX
// TodoListDisplay.jsx
import { usePowerSync } from "@powersync/react";

export const TodoListDisplay = () => {
    const powersync = usePowerSync();

    const [lists, setLists] = React.useState([]);

    React.useEffect(() => {
        powersync.getAll('SELECT * from lists').then(setLists)
    }, []);

    return <ul>
        {lists.map(list => <li key={list.id}>{list.name}</li>)}
    </ul>
    }
```
